http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Samudaya-to-present-dance-drama-today/article13998547.ece

Artists of Samudaya theatre repertory are present a dance-drama focussing on the history and evolution of Kannada literature, titled “Kavya Ranga”, at the Sahyadri Arts and Commerce College here on January 14. The programme is scheduled to commence at 10.30 a.m.In the evening, the Samudaya artists will be staging a drama, titled “Mrutyunjaya”, at the Kuvempu Rangamandir here.The drama is based on the novels written by renowned litterateur Niranjana.The show will commence at 7 p.m. Sripad Bhat has directed the drama.